Off to Texas for a few days!! One of my favorite parts of traveling is the flight! ✈️✈️✈️ I know a lot of people are afraid of flights but I love that feeling of excitement when I’m going somewhere different. I have a ritual that I do every time I fly. Right when the plane departures, I mean exactly when the wheels stop touching the ground I make the sign of the cross and I do the same when the plane arrives! I’ve started doing that many years ago and never stopped! I do get people staring at me sometimes but I don’t care! I do it anyway! 😂 Do you like to fly?

She was on Rocky the whole time so kudos to mommy for keeping Valentina comfortable the whole time. @southwestair was so nice to us and gave us great advice in making our trip very easy. Shout out to Yukon, OK!!!! I love it, most people might be like-“where?!” That’s where I live girl! I hope you loved your visit, the people are crazy nice here-it was one of the 1st things I noticed when we moved out here, I could stay forever!
You forgot where you just went last week🤣
Everything is amazing in DC! We love it there!!!! If you can pop over to Georgetown it’s so lovely!!!
Anything specific you do while your pregnant and flying?

The zoo! If I remember correctly it’s free 😁 and I heard it’s a good one. We didn’t have our daughter with us in July or we would have gone. The Segway and bike tours are amazing but with the little guy that will be challenging unless you have someone that will keep him. The top of the trump hotel has a tower that looks over the entire city, used to be a post office a very long time ago. There are tons of things to do, lots of museums and activities. Lots of great restaurants too 😁
I freaking LOVE DC!!! Our favorite restaurant is @busboysandpoets ! Great food, amazing atmosphere, and an awesome bookstore✌🏽
I loooooove DC. But I mostly love that you can just pop over to Maryland for all the blue crab you can eat 🤤
@megmarsh810 get up to pee/walk every hour, compression socks! And sometimes where a mask if it’s flu season 💙
All of the Smithsonian Museums are free including the zoo - the World Series is this weekend in DC so be prepared for excess crowds in some parts!!
@cmsbarro10 we have the wedding Saturday and Sunday in Rockville MD so we should miss most of that!
You went to Pagosa Springs?! That’s where we went for part of vacation last month!!
Old town Alexandria is my home❤️❤️ we’re missing it terribly!
@lauraraeschaller Ben’s mom has a house there!! We were there this week, last year!!
@the_sugar_butcher we’re actually staying in Rockville MD! Seafood rec??

@brittkovacs there’s so many great places! Maryland Blue Crab House is great because you can order them by the dozen (small, med or large crabs) and Bo Brooks! But honestly blue crab is just one of those things you can’t get in California and in my opinion you can’t go wrong with any place you choose to go eat it that’s near where you’re staying! It’s the BEST CRAB.
